ok so apparently @roblabla changed his server from spigot to vanilla. So spigot probably doesn't work.

The JSON message returned by spigot is not parsed correctly:

```
{ extra: [ { color: 'yellow', text: 'bot1 joined the game' } ], text: '' }
{ extra: [ '<user1> hello' ], text: '' }
```

All tested with the current master.

So : yeah client_echo chat parsing doesn't work, not surprising, parsing chat is a bit complicated now, even mineflayer doesn't parse all kind of chat yet. ( #154 )

But thanks to recent commits to fix proxy on us.mineplex.com, spigot now seems fixed (bot correctly spawn and it can be seen in tab)

title: Does node-minecraft-protocol work with spigot ?
